issues.title: Carbon Buildup on Intake Valves
issues.description: Direct injection engines in the GS 350 are prone to carbon buildup on intake valves, which can cause rough idle, misfires, and reduced performance. This is common in direct injection engines as fuel doesn't clean the valves.
issues.fix_description: Professional walnut blasting or chemical cleaning of intake valves every 60,000-80,000 miles
issues.prevention: Use top-tier gasoline, occasional Italian tune-ups (highway driving), consider fuel system cleaners

issues.title: Melting Dashboard
issues.description: The dashboard surface can become sticky, melted, or warped, particularly in hot climates. This affects the area around the instrument cluster and center console.
issues.fix_description: Dashboard replacement or professional refinishing service
issues.prevention: Use dashboard covers, park in shade, use window tinting

issues.title: Rear Main Seal Oil Leak
issues.description: The rear main seal can develop leaks, causing oil to drip onto the ground. This issue typically occurs in higher mileage vehicles and can worsen over time.
symptoms: oil visible on transmission bell housing
issues.fix_description: Replace rear main seal, requires transmission removal
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with proper viscosity oil, avoid overfilling oil

issues.title: Water Pump Failure
issues.description: The water pump can fail prematurely, especially around 80,000-120,000 miles, leading to coolant leaks and potential engine overheating.
issues.fix_description: Replace water pump, typically done with timing belt service
issues.prevention: Regular coolant flushes, monitor coolant levels, address leaks promptly

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing
issues.description: The Remote Touch Interface and navigation system can freeze, become unresponsive, or display error messages. Screen may go black or buttons become non-functional.
issues.fix_description: Software update, system reset, or module replacement if hardware failure
issues.prevention: Keep system updated, avoid extreme temperatures, gentle operation of controls

issues.title: Brake Actuator Failure
issues.description: The brake actuator assembly can fail, causing loss of power braking assistance and potentially longer stopping distances. This is a safety-critical issue.
issues.fix_description: Replace brake actuator assembly, may be covered under extended warranty
issues.prevention: Regular brake fluid changes, prompt attention to brake warnings

issues.title: Air Suspension Compressor Failure
issues.description: Vehicles equipped with air suspension may experience compressor failure, leading to uneven ride height and poor ride quality. More common in higher mileage vehicles.
issues.fix_description: Replace air suspension compressor or convert to conventional springs
issues.prevention: Avoid overloading vehicle, address leaks promptly, regular inspection

issues.title: Fuel Injector Carbon Fouling
issues.description: Direct injection fuel injectors can become clogged with carbon deposits, causing rough idle, misfires, and reduced fuel economy.
issues.fix_description: Professional fuel injector cleaning or replacement
issues.prevention: Use top-tier gasoline, periodic fuel system cleaning, avoid short trips

issues.title: Door Handle Chrome Peeling
issues.description: Chrome plating on exterior door handles can peel, bubble, or flake off, particularly in harsh weather conditions or with frequent use.
issues.fix_description: Replace door handles or professional refinishing
issues.prevention: Regular waxing, avoid harsh chemicals, gentle use

issues.title: Steering Rack Oil Leak
issues.description: Power steering rack can develop leaks at the seals, causing power steering fluid loss and potential steering difficulties.
issues.fix_description: Replace steering rack or rebuild with new seals
issues.prevention: Regular power steering fluid changes, avoid hitting curbs

issues.title: Transmission Shift Hesitation
issues.description: The 8-speed automatic transmission may exhibit hesitation or delayed shifts, particularly when cold or during light acceleration.
issues.fix_description: Transmission software update or fluid change, valve body service in severe cases
issues.prevention: Regular transmission fluid changes, gentle driving during warm-up

editorial.hero_blurb: The GS 350 represents Lexus at its most balanced, combining a silky-smooth V6 with athletic handling and signature reliability. This is the thinking enthusiast's luxury sedan - sophisticated enough for the boardroom, engaging enough for the back roads.
editorial.essence: The GS 350 strikes the perfect equilibrium between luxury comfort and sporting capability. Its naturally aspirated V6 delivers linear power while the chassis rewards spirited driving without sacrificing ride quality.
editorial.heritage: The fourth-generation GS marked Lexus's commitment to dynamic excellence, building on decades of LS luxury expertise while incorporating F Sport DNA. This generation represented a bold departure from the conservative GS reputation.
editorial.design_philosophy: Lexus pursued 'L-finesse' design language with aggressive spindle grille styling and athletic proportions, creating a visual statement that backed up the car's newfound sporting pretensions while maintaining executive presence.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not directly race-bred, the GS platform shares DNA with Lexus's Super GT and endurance racing programs, with lessons learned from track competition influencing suspension tuning and aerodynamic development.
editorial.engine_character: The 2GR-FSE V6 is a masterclass in refinement, delivering power with creamy smoothness and a distinctive intake growl. It builds momentum progressively, feeling effortless rather than explosive, with remarkable consistency across the rev range.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 6-speed automatic shifts with deliberate precision, holding gears longer in Sport mode while remaining imperceptibly smooth in comfort settings. Manual mode provides satisfying paddle control without the harshness of sportier boxes.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The GS chassis strikes an ideal compromise between comfort and control, with adaptive dampers that can transform character instantly. Body roll is well-controlled while still allowing natural weight transfer communication.
editorial.steering_feel: Variable-ratio electric steering provides good road surface feedback with appropriately weighted feel that builds confidence through corners. It's not the most communicative setup but delivers precision and consistency.
editorial.brake_confidence: Four-wheel disc brakes offer strong, progressive stopping power with excellent pedal feel. The system inspires confidence in both daily driving and more spirited scenarios without being overly aggressive.
editorial.sound_signature: The V6 produces a cultured intake note that builds to a purposeful growl under acceleration, while maintaining luxury-car refinement at cruise. It's sophisticated rather than shouty, befitting the car's character.
editorial.ideal_owner: Executive drivers who appreciate understated performance, value reliability over flashiness, and want a luxury sedan that can handle both business meetings and weekend canyon runs with equal aplomb.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Badge-conscious buyers seeking German prestige, those wanting cutting-edge technology, or drivers prioritizing maximum performance over refined balance and reliability.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for well-maintained examples with service history, as the V6 rewards proper care. The GS 350 offers exceptional value in the used luxury sedan market while delivering genuine driver satisfaction.
